<topic id="ch_css_combinators">
    <title>CSS Combinators</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>CSS<indexterm>combinators</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
    <body>
        <p>A selector is a chain of one or more sequences of simple selectors that can be separated
      by combinators. By combining simple selectors they gives them a useful relationship to each
      other and the content location in the document.</p>
    <p id="p_wtv_dgk_54b">The following table summarizes the combinators supported by <ph
        keyref="product"/>:<table id="table_nnv_mpt_cbb" frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
        <tgroup cols="4">
          <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" colwidth="2.25*"/>
          <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2" colwidth="9.01*"/>
          <colspec colnum="3" colname="col3" colwidth="3.14*"/>
          <colspec colnum="4" colname="col4" colwidth="1*" align="center"/>
          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry>Pattern</entry>
              <entry>Meaning</entry>
              <entry>Described in section</entry>
              <entry>CSS level</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry>E F</entry>
              <entry>An <xmlelement>F</xmlelement> element descendant of an
                  <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element</entry>
              <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#descendant-combinators"
                  format="html" scope="external">Descendant combinator</xref></entry>
              <entry>1</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>E > F</entry>
              <entry>An <xmlelement>F</xmlelement> element child of an element
                  <xmlelement>E</xmlelement></entry>
              <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#child-combinators" format="html"
                  scope="external">Child combinator</xref></entry>
              <entry>2</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>E + F</entry>
              <entry>An <xmlelement>F</xmlelement> element immediately preceded by an element
                  <xmlelement>E</xmlelement></entry>
              <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#adjacent-sibling-combinators"
                  format="html" scope="external"> Next-sibling combinator</xref></entry>
              <entry>2</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>E ~ F</entry>
              <entry>An <xmlelement>F</xmlelement> element preceded by an element
                  <xmlelement>E</xmlelement></entry>
              <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#general-sibling-combinators"
                  format="html" scope="external"> Subsequent-sibling combinator</xref></entry>
              <entry>3</entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </table></p>
